      • updateCloseState

        public void updateCloseState(boolean close,
                    boolean local)
        Description copied from interface: IStream

        A stream can be open, half closed or closed and this method updates the close state of this stream.

        If the stream is open, calling this method with a value of true puts the stream into half closed state.

        If the stream is half closed, calling this method with a value of true puts the stream into closed state.

        Specified by:
        updateCloseState in interface IStream
        Parameters:
        close - whether the close state should be updated
        local - whether the close is local or remote
